File: Sports and Arts and Culture Minister, Nathi Mthethwa. JOHANNESBURG - Sports, Arts and Culture Minister, Nathi Mthethwa, has gazetted the rules for arts and cultural spaces. The new directives form part of amended Level 3 lockdown regulations. South Africans can once again visit cinemas, theatres, museums, libraries and galleries. Cinemas, theatres libraries and galleries will only be allowed to admit 50 patrons. LIST: Changes to level 3 regulations They will have to wear masks at all times except while eating. Venues will have to ensure social distancing and must provide sanitisers. The gazette also includes rules for sports. READ: COVID-19: SA infections at over 200,000 Contact and non-contact sport may also resume without any spectators. All athletes and support staff will have to be tested for COVID-19 before the resumption of any sporting code. But, bodies will have to write to the Minister within 14 days to apply to resume. Department of Sport, Arts and Culture - Government Gazette No. 751 by eNCA.com on Scribd  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.